## The problem most business owners do not talk about

You are good at your trade. That is not the issue. The issue is everything that happens around the trade — the calls you miss when you are on a job, the follow-ups you forget, the quotes that go cold because you ran out of time.

These are not failures of effort. They are failures of system.

## What automation actually means

Automation does not mean robots replacing people. It means the routine, repetitive tasks — sending a reminder, following up a missed call, asking for a review — happen without you having to remember them.

You set them up once. They run forever.

## Three automations every UK trade business should have first

**1. Missed call text-back.** When you miss a call on the job, the system sends a text within 30 seconds: "Sorry I missed your call — how can I help?" That lead is not lost.

**2. Appointment reminders.** The system texts your clients 24 hours before and 2 hours before. No-shows drop by up to 60%.

**3. Review requests.** 24 hours after a job is complete, the system sends a text asking for a Google review. Your rating grows on autopilot.

